tests.name: Zinc (Zn)
tests.description: Essential trace element important for immune function, wound healing, and enzyme activity.

tests.name: Thyroid Stimulating Hormone (TSH)
tests.description: Hormone produced by the pituitary gland that regulates thyroid activity.

tests.name: Free Thyroxine (FT4)
tests.description: Active form of thyroid hormone that controls metabolism and energy production.

tests.name: Anti-Thyroid Peroxidase Antibodies (Anti-TPO)
tests.description: Autoantibodies that may indicate autoimmune thyroid disease.

tests.name: 25-Hydroxyvitamin D (Vitamin D total)
tests.description: Vitamin D status, important for bone health, immune function, and calcium absorption.

tests.name: Prolactin (PRL)
tests.description: Hormone involved in lactation and reproductive system regulation.

tests.name: Total Testosterone
tests.description: Sex hormone affecting libido, muscle mass, and bone strength.

tests.name: Androstenedione
tests.description: Hormone precursor for testosterone and estrogen production.

tests.name: Vitamin B12 (Cyanocobalamin)
tests.description: Vitamin essential for red blood cell formation and nervous system function.

tests.name: Folic Acid
tests.description: Vitamin B9, important for DNA synthesis and cell division.

tests.name: Dihydrotestosterone
tests.description: Potent androgen hormone derived from testosterone, affecting hair growth and sexual development.
